Comment: Very good puzzle for clash of code !
I think that the public example is a bit light for clash of code reverse mode. A second example would be great for understanding. Otherwise, it's a good chall for clash of code as Manuel J. says

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: Good for clash of code

Goal
* Please change "the list" to "the given list of non-negative integers".

Input / Output
* Please change "Ligne" to "Line" (3 times).

Constraints
* Please add:
The list contains at least one non-prime number in each case.

Cases
* Each pair of cases should be similar to each other. Please revise as follows:

• Test 1: ok
• Validator 1: Fewer numbers with the list containing numbers less than 10 only

• Test 2: Change the list to "0 1".
• Validator 2: ok.

• Test 3: ok.
• Validator 3: Copy Test 4 here (n = 10, the list is 15 13 78 44 36 37 11 97 31 77).

• Test 4: Revise the case such that 20 ≤ n ≤ 25 and **only one** non-prime number is in the list. All the other numbers in the list are unique prime numbers (i.e. no duplicates).
• Validator 4: Similar to the new Test 4.

Add:
• Test 5: Copy Test 2 here (n = 76).
• Validator 5: Revise the case such that n ≥ 70 with a good mix of numbers in the list, similar to the original Test 2.

Thanks.
